<paragraph blockId="8.[313,1269,181,970]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1190">
The 
<collectingCountry box="[407,516,787,811]" name="Barbados" pageId="8" pageNumber="1190">Barbados</collectingCountry>
specimens described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Gosliner" authorityYear="1979" box="[801,898,787,811]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cuthonidae" genus="Cuthona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="1190" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perca">
<emphasis box="[801,898,787,811]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1190">C. perca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Marcus and Hughes (1974) differ greatly in colour and radular tooth shape from the descriptions of this species based on specimens found elsewhere (Marcus, 1958; Edmunds, 1964; Gosliner, 1979; Perrone, 1995). Further specimens of the same species collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[1159,1268,883,907]" name="Barbados" pageId="8" pageNumber="1190">Barbados</collectingCountry>
some years later were determined as being different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Gosliner" authorityYear="1979" box="[957,1050,915,938]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cuthonidae" genus="Cuthona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="1190" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perca">
<emphasis box="[957,1050,915,938]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1190">C. perca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and related species and thus described as a new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Edmunds and Just, 1983" authorityName="Edmunds and Just" authorityYear="1983" box="[739,1261,946,970]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cuthonidae" genus="Cuthona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="1190" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="barbadiana">
<emphasis box="[739,966,946,970]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1190">Cuthona barbadiana</emphasis>
Edmunds and Just, 1983
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
